<subSubSection id="6587886CA90547D45C01868F90BE5738" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="12A15FE4B13DCBE59F4CCF0CA97B7F6F" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="55CBED698823EC6E7FAD3230758A2F65" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
This is a species with an European distribution (
<bibRefCitation id="AF0099DC6BDBD8A78D25CBA9977A8558" author="Hamilton, A. P." journalOrPublisher="Cambridge University Press, Cambridge" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668218" refString="Hamilton, A. P., 1980. Flora Europaea Vol. 5. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge" title="Flora Europaea Vol. 5" year="1980">Hamilton 1980</bibRefCitation>
), known locally from the floristic regions of Southern Pindos (SPi), Northern Pindos (NPi), Sterea Ellas (StE) and North East (NE; 
<bibRefCitation id="7F9F01820F70647F05F5A1553388E6C0" author="Dimopoulos, P." journalOrPublisher="Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Berlin; Hellenic Botanical Society, Athens" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668013" refString="Dimopoulos, P., Raus, T., Bergmeier, E., Constantinidis, T., Iatrou, G., Kokkini, S., Strid, A., D.Tzanoudakis, , 2013. Vascular plants of Greece: An annotated checklist. Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Berlin; Hellenic Botanical Society, Athens" title="Vascular plants of Greece: An annotated checklist" year="2013">Dimopoulos et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
). The population on Mt. Vermio is the first recorded from the floristic region of North Central (NC) Greece. Plants from this new population are rather slender, with congested inflorescences consisting of 3-6 flowers.
</paragraph>
